The '''1969 Libyan Constitution''' was brought into force on 11 December 1969 by the [[Libyan Revolutionary Command Council|Revolutionary Command Council]], in the name of the [[Arab people]] of the [[Libyan Arab Republic]]. The [[constitution]] would remain in force until the adoption of the [[Libyan interim Constitutional Declaration|interim constitution]] on 3 August 2011.

