{{wiktionary|dago}}

'''DAGO''' is an acronym which stands for '''D'''epartment of the '''A'''rmy '''G'''eneral '''O'''fficer.  It is not typically used outside of the [[Department of the Army]] headquarters and staff sections, however it is sometimes seen in memorandums and other forms of correspondence to lower level [[wiktionary:en:echelon|echelons]].  It is also sometimes used to refer to [[General]] Officers that are part of the Department of the Army by personnel that are within other sections of the [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]].

There are also certain orders issued by the Department of the Army that are called DAGOs or '''D'''epartment of the '''A'''rmy '''G'''eneral '''O'''rders that pertain to base closures, unit citations, the creation of JROTC units, certain awards such as the Medal of Honor and Legion of Merit and structural changes to the Army.  These are listed by year on the Army Publishing Directorate's website.

